13.What is the difference between Active and Passive deletion in W365 Cloud PC
(3 Points)
Ans. Active deletion in Windows 365 occurs when an administrator or user manually deletes
a Cloud PC or removes a license while the subscription is active, triggering a 30-day data
retention period.
Passive deletion in Windows 365 occurs when a subscription ends or a license remains
unassigned for an extended period, leading to automatic data deletion within 90 to 180
days. This differs from active deletion (immediate admin action) by acting as a retention
grace period rather than an immediate removal of user data and Cloud PC disks.
